08:24.962 --> 08:26.802
and not the service.

08:26.804 --> 08:28.454
Hmm, although, I just wish
someone would tell me,

08:28.456 --> 08:30.642
whenever I order
just a simple cup of coffee,

08:30.644 --> 08:33.100
I am presented with
every, like, condiment

08:33.102 --> 08:34.212
known to mankind.

08:35.445 --> 08:38.284
That's because
it has been decreed

08:38.285 --> 08:39.859
by the mistress
of the inn.

08:39.861 --> 08:41.702
Who?

08:41.703 --> 08:42.931
Mrs. Quinn.

08:42.933 --> 08:44.236
Mrs. Quinn?

08:44.238 --> 08:45.657
As you will
have noticed, ladies,

08:45.659 --> 08:46.924
for the past week,

08:46.926 --> 08:49.305
the famous New York writer,
Mr. Harry Quebert,

08:49.307 --> 08:51.264
has been coming here every day,

08:51.266 --> 08:52.492
which means

08:52.494 --> 08:54.297
he sees in our restaurant

08:54.299 --> 08:56.371
the standards
of quality and refinement

08:56.373 --> 08:57.906
found in the best establishments

08:57.908 --> 08:59.942
on the East Coast.

08:59.944 --> 09:01.593
Now, I have written a memo

09:01.595 --> 09:04.473
to remind you of how Mr. Quebert
should be treated.

09:04.475 --> 09:05.664
Read it,

09:05.666 --> 09:07.238
reread it,

09:07.240 --> 09:08.505
and learn it by heart.

09:08.507 --> 09:11.922
"Do not disturb Mr. Quebert

09:11.924 --> 09:14.534
because he needs calm and...

09:14.536 --> 09:16.838
concentration.

09:16.840 --> 09:19.065
His previous visits to Clark's

09:19.067 --> 09:22.290
indicate that he always orders
black coffee.

09:22.292 --> 09:24.402
Serve him coffee
when he arrives,

09:24.404 --> 09:26.437
and nothing else..."

09:26.439 --> 09:30.201
Do not bother Mr. Quebert
by suggesting he order food.

09:30.203 --> 09:31.698
However,

09:31.700 --> 09:33.965
serve him
all the condiments we have,

09:33.967 --> 09:35.884
so should he be
inclined to order,

09:35.886 --> 09:38.457
he won't have to
ask for them.

09:38.459 --> 09:41.106
You see, famous writers
should not have to ask

09:41.108 --> 09:42.604
for what they want.

09:42.606 --> 09:46.252
Their minds must be free
to create.

09:46.254 --> 09:47.673
"It is possible

09:47.675 --> 09:50.669
that what he's writing
will become a masterpiece,

09:50.671 --> 09:53.318
and Clark's will be known
all over the country!"

09:53.320 --> 09:55.123
Is this one of
the best restaurants?

09:55.125 --> 09:55.929
Yes, Mrs. Quinn.

09:55.931 --> 09:56.850
Yes, Mom.

09:56.852 --> 09:58.770
And don't call me "Mom," okay?

09:58.772 --> 10:00.153
It's not
a country inn.

10:00.155 --> 10:01.382
Good.

10:01.384 --> 10:03.186
Now, I want to see you all
acting servile.

10:03.188 --> 10:05.298
And smile.

10:05.300 --> 10:07.526
Ah. Beautiful.

10:07.528 --> 10:08.908
Let's do a trial run.

10:08.910 --> 10:12.287
I will play
the esteemed Mr. Quebert.

10:12.289 --> 10:14.209
Come on!

10:16.667 --> 10:19.084
<i>In Sommerdale,
I was some sort of celebrity.</i>

10:19.086 --> 10:22.847
<i>In New York, I was just
a high school teacher</i>

10:22.849 --> 10:25.766
<i>who wrote a good first book
in his spare time,</i>

10:25.768 --> 10:27.839
<i>but people in town
assumed I was successful</i>

10:27.841 --> 10:31.257
<i>because of the way I acted
and where I lived.</i>

10:31.259 --> 10:32.985
Hey!

10:32.987 --> 10:34.905
<i>Not everyone
was fooled, though...</i>

10:34.907 --> 10:36.632
Hey, Ernie!

10:36.634 --> 10:38.016
What do you do
in New York, actually?

10:38.018 --> 10:39.858
For a living, I mean?

10:39.860 --> 10:41.780
Well, I'm a writer.

10:43.278 --> 10:45.273
Uh...

10:45.275 --> 10:48.767
Well, don't take this
the wrong way, Harry,

10:48.769 --> 10:50.764
but, uh, I contacted
the publisher,

10:50.766 --> 10:53.529
the one
who put out your book.

10:53.531 --> 10:55.756
The one you gave me,
"The Mirror of Life."

10:55.758 --> 10:59.827
I-I wanted to order
extra copies for the library.

10:59.829 --> 11:02.860
I hadn't heard of this
publisher before, but...

11:02.862 --> 11:05.663
then I discovered
that it was actually a...

11:05.665 --> 11:07.276
a print shop in Brooklyn.

11:07.278 --> 11:11.118
You paid a print shop
to publish your book.

11:18.722 --> 11:21.868
Now you know the truth.

11:21.870 --> 11:24.902
I'm a... complete impostor.

11:24.904 --> 11:28.089
No, not complete.

11:28.091 --> 11:29.702
I...

11:29.704 --> 11:31.624
I really liked the book.

11:32.007 --> 11:35.999
That's why I wanted
to order extra copies.

11:36.001 --> 11:39.301
And, uh...
anyway, who knows?

11:39.303 --> 11:40.876
Maybe the book
you're writing now

11:40.878 --> 11:42.988
will be a masterpiece.

11:42.990 --> 11:44.063
What if
I don't write it?

11:44.065 --> 11:46.060
Aw, you will.
I know you will.

11:46.062 --> 11:47.135
And don't worry, I, uh,

11:47.137 --> 11:49.288
I won't tell a soul
about my discovery.

11:52.322 --> 11:54.242
On one condition.

11:55.547 --> 11:58.117
Uh... I want, uh...

11:58.119 --> 12:03.033
you to, uh, put my name
on the last page of your book,

12:03.035 --> 12:05.145
as a "thank you,"
y-you know how writers do?

12:05.147 --> 12:06.719
Mm-hm.

12:06.721 --> 12:09.062
And, uh...

12:09.064 --> 12:11.481
I want to be
the first one mentioned,

12:11.483 --> 12:13.248
in big letters.

12:13.250 --> 12:15.782
I think it would make
my wife proud

12:15.784 --> 12:17.932
to see that I contributed
to the success

12:17.934 --> 12:19.892
of a literary masterpiece.

12:22.581 --> 12:23.999
Okay.

12:24.001 --> 12:25.381
You have yourself a deal.

12:26.843 --> 12:29.913
<i>I wanted to tell Nola
the whole truth,</i>

12:29.915 --> 12:32.104
<i>but vanity
got the better of me.</i>

12:35.061 --> 12:37.478
Then, when "The Origin of Evil"
was published,

12:37.480 --> 12:40.857
I'd go all over
the world, you know?

12:40.859 --> 12:43.775
I'd always look for her,

12:43.777 --> 12:46.350
hoping she'd be
somewhere in the crowd.

12:48.654 --> 12:51.493
I still...

12:51.495 --> 12:52.645
hoped,

12:52.647 --> 12:55.602
up until the day they...

12:55.604 --> 12:59.020
